MeshCore for Tanmatsu — Authors and Contributors
==================================================

Lead author
-----------
CJ van Soest <CJvanSoest@users.noreply.github.com>
  Project conception, BadgeVMS/Tanmatsu integration, protocol RE work,
  UI/UX, NVS / SD storage, multi-channel + region-scope, ACK tracking,
  emoji rendering, app icon.

AI co-author
------------
Claude (Anthropic)
  Pair-programming partner for design discussions, code generation,
  reverse-engineering of MeshCore protocol details, devlog entries.

Contributors
------------
Ilias el Matani <hello@ilias.codes>
  Component architecture refactor (the mc_* components + build-enforced
  layering), the mc_crypto extraction, host-test suite expansion, the
  GitHub Actions CI and the arch-rules / structure lints, documentation.

Upstream MeshCore protocol
--------------------------
Scott Powell / rippleradios.com — original MeshCore C++ implementation
Nicolai Electronics — Tanmatsu adaptation + companion_radio firmware
Renze (MeshCore Discord) — protocol Q&A: channel key derivation,
                            transport_codes / region scope confirmations.

Third-party assets
------------------
Lode Vandevenne — lodepng PNG decoder (zlib)
Project Nayuki — qrcodegen library (MIT)
Daniel J. Bernstein et al. — ed25519 reference code (public domain)
Twitter / jdecked — Twemoji emoji bitmaps (CC-BY 4.0)
robotman2412 / Badge.Team — pax-gfx graphics library (MIT)

If you contributed code, art, ideas, field testing, or bug reports and
want to be listed here, open an issue or PR with your preferred attribution.
